===============================================================================
                      EQUIPMENT - Weapons and Armor
===============================================================================

WEAPONS
-------
Weapons increase your damage in combat. You can only wield ONE weapon at a time.

To equip a weapon:
  wield <weapon name>
  Example: wield sword

To unequip a weapon:
  unwield

Available weapons you might find:
  Iron Sword   - 25 damage (sold at blacksmith, or find one)
  Rat Tooth    - 3 damage (dropped by rats)
  Snake Fang   - 5 damage (dropped by snakes)

Weapon damage formula:
  Total damage = Weapon damage + (STR / 2)

ARMOR
-----
Armor reduces damage you take in combat. You can wear multiple pieces in
different slots.

Armor slots:
  Head    - Helmets, caps, hoods
  Torso   - Shirts, chainmail, robes
  Hands   - Gloves, gauntlets
  Legs    - Pants, greaves (future)
  Feet    - Boots, shoes (future)

To equip armor:
  wear <armor name>
  Example: wear leather cap

To remove armor:
  remove <armor name>
  remove <slot name>
  Example: remove cap, remove head

Available armor you might find:
  Leather Cap  - AC 1, head slot (buy at shops)
  Wolf Pelt    - AC 2, torso slot (dropped by wolves)
  Web Gloves   - AC 1, hands slot (dropped by spiders)

Armor damage reduction:
  Damage taken = Incoming damage - Total armor class
  (You always take at least 1 damage)

INVENTORY MANAGEMENT
--------------------
  inventory   - See what you're carrying and wearing
  get <item>  - Pick up an item from the ground
  drop <item> - Drop an item from your inventory

Notes:
  - You cannot drop a wielded weapon (unwield it first)
  - You cannot drop worn armor (remove it first)
  - Items on your corpse can be looted by anyone!

See also: help wield, help wear, help inventory, help combat
===============================================================================
